b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe15079.htm)  [Next](sbe15081.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n[Buy this Book at\nAmazon.com](http://www.amazon.com/exec/obidos/ASIN/B002DEMBWG/internetsacredte)\n\n* * *\n\n[![](../../img/tn_hin.jpg)](index.htm)  \n_The Upanishads, Part 2 (SBE15)_ , by Max Muller, [1879], at sacred-texts.com\n\n* * *\n\n### SECOND BR\xc3\x82HMA _N_ A.\n\n1\\. The threefold descendants of Pra _g_ apati, gods, men, and Asuras (evil\nspirits), dwelt as; Brahma _k_ arins (students) with their father Pra _g_\napati. Having finished their studentship the gods said: \'Tell us (something),\nSir.\' He told them the syllable Da. Then he said: \'Did you understand?\' They\nsaid: \'We did understand. You told us "Damyata," Be subdued.\' \'Yes,\' he said,\n\'you have understood.\'\n\n2\\. Then the men said to him: \'Tell us something,\n\np. 190\n\n[paragraph continues] Sir.\' He told them the same syllable Da. Then he said:\n\'Did you understand?\' They said: \'We did understand. You told us, "Datta,"\nGive.\' \'Yes,\' he said, \'you have understood.\'\n\n3\\. Then the Asuras said to him: \'Tell us something, Sir.\' He told them the\nsame syllable Da. Then he said: \'Did you understand?\' They said: \'We did\nunderstand. You told us, "Dayadham," Be merciful.\' \'Yes,\' he said, \'you have\nunderstood.\'\n\nThe divine voice of thunder repeats the same, Da Da Da, that is, Be subdued,\nGive, Be merciful. Therefore let that triad be taught, Subduing, Giving, and\nMercy.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: V, 3](sbe15081.htm)\n\n'